status_message: Robotics is all set to change the way we look at life, making it all the more easy. Meet the Indian startups innovating in the field of robotics, only at #StartupIndia pavilion, Hall #18, IITF 2017.

The India International Trade Fair (IITF) being hosted from 14th to 27th of November at Pragati Maidan, New Delhi. IITF with B2B and B2C components is one of the largest integrated trade fairs. The format of IITF has Business, Social, Cultural and Educational Dimensions that are weaved together where visitors and exhibitors, media persons, marketing professionals, social activists, NGOs etc. all come together to explore their objectives.
 
Several Government Organizations use this platform to spread awareness about their programs and policies among the public. As such, almost all States and Union Territories of Federal Government of India participate in this mega event. The theme this year is Startup India and Stand Up India
 
Open to Business Visitors from Nov 14-17 | General-Public from Nov 18-27 | 9.30 am to 7.30 pm

About Start Up India pavilion:

Set up in Hall 18, Pragati Maidan, will be the Start Up India pavilion where we will showcase indigenous start-ups across various industries. The pavilion is also going to host some of the latest-in-tech engagements activities such as; The Sling Shot and Tweet Caf√©!

Visit us at hall 18, Pragati Maidan to witness the giant leap our indigenous start-ups are making.
Today's #startups are creating tomorrow's India. Meet such promising startups at IITF 2017. Visit the #StartupIndia pavilion at Hall #18.
